[thinking] I’m looking into why the native-image run is failing. It seems that setup requires certain system properties, and the current test scaffold already has custom runtime arguments for version 5.0.0, which need to be updated for 5.0.1 as well. There’s some uncertainty about whether “sun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow” is actually a valid Java system property, but it looks like existing uses may interpret it correctly. I might need to ensure that tests provide a JSON output with actions and guidance to address this effectively.
[thinking] 
